      "value": "<p>&gt;@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.RmU5en0JokeQXJyP]{Spy}</p>\n<p>At 11th level, whenever you succeed at a saving throw against a spell, technological device, or ability that would provide information about you (such as @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.spells.Item.moyeAHT4yzZVWmmg]{Detect Thoughts}), instead of negating the effect, you can provide false information that matches your cover identity. If such an effect has no saving throw, you can attempt a Bluff check opposed by the Sense Motive check of the caster or user, and provide similar false information on a success.</p>"
